This paper is about object segmentation and fine-grained localization using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new method for feature representation using hypercolumns, which involves combining information from multiple layers of the CNN. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper presents experimental results on three different tasks, which could make it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
